{{Infobox Politician | name = Harold E. Welsh | image = | caption = | office = [[Legislative Assembly of Ontario|Ontario MPP]] | term_start = 1936 | term_end = 1943 | predecessor = [[James Ferguson Hill]] | successor = [[Roscoe Robson]] | constituency = [[Hastings East (provincial electoral district)|Hastings East]] | party = [[Progressive Conservative Party of Ontario|Progressive Conservative]] | birth_date = {{birth date|1897|12|5}} | birth_place = [[Moira, Ontario]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1964|4|1|1897|12|5}} | death_place = [[Algonquin Park]], [[Ontario]] | occupation = Physician | spouse = | children = }} '''Harold Edward Welsh''' (May 5, 1896 &ndash; May 20, 1943) was a politician in [[Ontario]], Canada. He was a [[Progressive Conservative Party of Ontario|Progressive Conservative]] member of the [[Legislative Assembly of Ontario]] from 1936 to 1943 who represented the eastern Ontario riding of [[Hastings East (provincial electoral district)|Hastings East]].
==Background== The son of William Frederick Welsh and Caroline Mabel Oatwater, he was born in [[Moira, Ontario]] and was educated at the [[University of Toronto]].<ref name="normandin">{{cite book |title=Canadian Parliamentary Guide, 1939 |year=1939 |last=Normandin |first=A L}}</ref> He worked as a country doctor, living in [[Roslin, Ontario|Roslin]] and also served as [[coroner]] for [[Hastings County, Ontario|Hastings County]] and as medical officer of health for Huntingdon, Thurlow and Tyendinaga townships.<ref name="cmaj">{{cite book |pmc=1827826 |title=Canadian Medical Association Journal |publisher=Canadian Medical Association |page=68 |date=July 1943 }}</ref><ref name="normandin"/>
==Politics== Welsh was elected to the assembly in 1936, defeating Liberal candidate Dr. Harold A. Boyce in a bitterly contested by-election held following the death of [[James Ferguson Hill]]. Liberal amendments altering the distribution of school taxes between public and Roman Catholic schools were a crucial issue in the by-election.<ref>{{cite journal |journal=Canadian Catholic Historical Association |url=http://www.umanitoba.ca/colleges/st_pauls/ccha/Back%20Issues/CCHA2002/Meehan.htm |title=The East Hastings By-Election of 1936 and the Ontario Separate School Tax Question |volume=68 |year=2002 |last=Meehan |first=Peter |pages=105–132}}</ref> Welsh died in office; he drowned while fishing in [[Algonquin Provincial Park]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=gRw_AAAAIBAJ&sjid=VE8MAAAAIBAJ&pg=6274,5411706 |page=2 |newspaper=Windsor Daily Star |title=Bitter By-election Recalled by Drowning |date=May 21, 1943 |accessdate=2011-07-06}}</ref>
